Redescription. Male. Head. Brown. Eyes abutting medially for length of three or four ommatidia. Antenna with plume setae well-developed, flagellomeres 1–4 separate, flagellomeres 5–8 fused, 10–13 (
Fig. 120
) elongate; flagellomere 13 with apical nipple slightly constricted basally; AR 0.85–1.16 ( 0.97 , n = 15 ). Palpus brown; segment 3 slender, moderately elongate, swollen at midlength, with subapical sensory pit; PR 2.78 –4.00 ( 3.47 , n = 16 ).

Thorax. dark brown, except pleura brown; scutellum with 5–6 strong setae. Legs pale brown; tarsomere 1 of hind tibia slightly swollen; hind tibial comb with 5 spines; foreleg TR 2.50–2.86 ( 2.71 , n = 16 ), midleg TR 2.22–2.375 ( 2.29 , n = 16 ), hind leg TR 2.33–2.78 ( 2.53 , n = 16 ); claws curved, moderately stout. Wing (
Fig. 121
) plain; vein M 2 not visible; intercalary vein visible; first radial cell obliterated, second well developed, narrow; fork of cubitus situated distad to level of apex of costa; wing length 0.70–1.12 ( 0.91 , n = 16 ) mm; breadth 0.24–0.36 ( 0.31 , n = 16 ) mm; CR 0.39–0.47 ( 0.40 , n = 16 ). Halter brown.

Abdomen. Tergites uniformly brown. Genitalia (
Fig. 122
): tergite 9 short, extending to 1 / 3 length of gonocoxite; posterior margin truncate; cercus slender, lobe-like; sternite 9 short with long anterolateral projections; posterior margin nearly straight, with scattered setae. Gonocoxite moderately stout, 2.2 X longer than greatest breadth; gonostylus 0.80 length of gonocoxite, slender, nearly straight, tip blunt. Parameres represented by posteromesally directed processes, the length variable but always shorter than length of aedeagus, each process gradually narrowed posterolaterally. Aedeagus (
Fig. 123
) broad, triangular, stout, tapering to conical, blunt tip; basal arch extending to 1 / 5 of total length.

Thorax. Dark brown; katepisternum light brown in some specimens, different from scutum, dark brown in others. Legs brown, some specimens with apical portion darker; tarsomere 1 of hind leg not swollen; foreleg TR 2.29–2.83 ( 2.55 , n = 16 ), midleg TR 2.06–2.43 ( 2.31 , n = 16 ), hind leg TR 2.22–2.75 ( 2.60 , n = 16 ), claws curved, moderately stout. Wing (
Fig. 126
) plain, without pattern of pigmented membrane; first radial cell obliterated; second radial cell well developed, narrow; fork of cubitus situated at level of apex of costa; wing length 0.54–1.02 ( 0.81 , n = 16 ) mm; breadth 0.24–0.46 ( 0.36 , n = 16 ) mm; CR 0.40–0.55 ( 0.44 , n = 16 ).

Abdomen. Tergites uniformly brown. Genital sclerotization (
Fig. 127
) quadrangular, lateral arms short. One spermatheca (
Fig. 128
) ovoid with recurved slender neck, heavily sclerotized, measuring 0.070 by 0.038 mm , including neck; one rudimentary spermatheca.
